<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key Eb (3 flats: Bb, Eb, Ab). "33" root triads primary; all diatonic.
- A° (non-diatonic in bar 2) → C major (④) substitution preserves subdominant function.
- Gm = ③m in bar 7 (approaching Cm ④m → Bb ⑤ → Eb ① cadence).
- LH: Eb2-Bb2-Eb3-G3 root position throughout Eb passages.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH Eb2 constant pedal anchors bars 1, 3, 5, 6, 8.
- RH climbs to Bb5-Eb5 at bars 3 and 5 (emotional peak), then steps down.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opens firmly bar 1 (full Eb triad). Builds to bar 5 peak (G5-Bb5 RH).
- Descent bars 6-8. Final Eb whole note bar 9 with full triad.
-->
